<h1>Misc</h1>
<p>Assets exposes some miscellaneous APIs for verifying the health (ping) and retrieving information (info) about the system.</p>

<a class=section name=ping></a>
<h2>Ping</h2>
<p>Returns ok if Assets is working properly. This is an endpoint that a health-check would want to monitor. Callers can either use the status code (<code>200</code>) or the basic response.</p>

<div class="tabs endpoint">
  <code>GET /ping</code>
  <ul>
    <li data-tab=res class=active>Response
    <li data-tab=sample_req>Sample Request
    <li data-tab=sample_res>Sample Response
    <li data-tab=errors>Errors
  </ul>
  <div data-tab=res>
    {% response [
      {name: 'ok', type: 'bool', desc: "<p>Should always be <code>true</code>.</p>"}
    ] %}
  </div>
  <div data-tab=sample_req>
    {% highlight "bash" %}
curl "http://127.0.0.1:5300/ping"
    {% endhighlight %}
  </div>
  <div data-tab=sample_res>
{% highlight "json" %}
{"ok":true}
{% endhighlight %}
  </div>
  <div data-tab=errors>
    {%- include './_errors.njk' %}
  </div>
</div>
<a class=section name=info></a>
<h2>Info</h2>
<p>Returns information about the system. The information included in the response is not sensitive and should be included in any bug reports.</p>

<div class="tabs endpoint">
  <code>GET /info</code>
  <ul>
    <li data-tab=res class=active>Response
    <li data-tab=sample_req>Sample Request
    <li data-tab=sample_res>Sample Response
    <li data-tab=errors>Errors
  </ul>
  <div data-tab=res>
    {% response [
      {name: 'go', type: 'string', desc: "<p>The version of Go used to build the system.</p>"},
      {name: 'commit', type: 'string', desc: "<p>The commit hash.</p>"}
    ] %}
  </div>
  <div data-tab=sample_req>
    {% highlight "bash" %}
curl "http://127.0.0.1:5300/info"
    {% endhighlight %}
  </div>
  <div data-tab=sample_res>
{% highlight "json" %}
{
  "go": "go1.19",
  "commit": "ce6d5c022ffd7834c6621a3a6522b8316bdf8c00"
}
{% endhighlight %}
  </div>
  <div data-tab=errors>
    {%- include './_errors.njk' %}
  </div>
</div>
